00:25:19.351 --> 00:25:20.684
Get him out of here.

260
00:25:23.396 --> 00:25:25.022
What the hell happened up there?

261
00:25:26.024 --> 00:25:27.191
Up here?

262
00:25:28.443 --> 00:25:30.819
I caught him trying to escape.

263
00:25:31.696 --> 00:25:33.113
Who the hell are you?

264
00:25:34.616 --> 00:25:36.867
Malone. Just transferred.
Right there.

265
00:25:37.077 --> 00:25:39.036
Yeah, check that out. Bam!

266
00:25:39.246 --> 00:25:40.454
-You know Malone?
-No.

267
00:25:40.622 --> 00:25:42.122
Nobody told me about it.

268
00:25:43.542 --> 00:25:44.750
Guys....

269
00:25:46.545 --> 00:25:49.421
-Sorry, ma'am.
-Excuse me.

270
00:25:51.132 --> 00:25:53.050
Let me flush, please.

271
00:25:56.471 --> 00:26:00.057
I didn't know.
You might not wanna go in there.

272
00:26:02.352 --> 00:26:04.853
You got some paperwork for me,
Malone?

273
00:26:05.981 --> 00:26:08.983
We've been requesting
a new detective for 8 months.

274
00:26:09.150 --> 00:26:13.279
Suddenly, you just turn up.
I'll never understand the system.

275
00:26:14.322 --> 00:26:17.783
Burglary? Sixteen citations,
mayor's commendation.

276
00:26:18.451 --> 00:26:20.661
You worked out of West Covina?

277
00:26:21.079 --> 00:26:22.997
Well, that's what it says right there.

278
00:26:23.790 --> 00:26:26.458
You look familiar, Malone.
Have we met before?

279
00:26:29.921 --> 00:26:32.798
You wouldn't happen to be
in a bowling league, would you?

280
00:26:34.968 --> 00:26:37.511
That's it. You're a bowler.

281
00:26:37.762 --> 00:26:40.514
-l try.
-We could use a guy in Burglary.

282
00:26:42.517 --> 00:26:43.892
Right here.

283
00:26:44.144 --> 00:26:48.647
I thought I was gonna be assigned
to a desk. Right up in here!

284
00:26:48.857 --> 00:26:49.982
Are you kidding me?

285
00:26:50.191 --> 00:26:53.319
A guy like you?
No, you belong on the street.

286
00:26:53.862 --> 00:26:54.862
And also, listen.

287
00:26:55.030 --> 00:26:58.907
Carlson needs a partner with some
experience. He just got promoted.

288
00:26:59.409 --> 00:27:00.909
Chief, I just got a call.

289
00:27:01.119 --> 00:27:03.704
Malone's gonna join us.
Show him around.

290
00:27:05.540 --> 00:27:08.042
And let Malone do
all the handcuffing, okay?

291
00:27:09.669 --> 00:27:11.045
I appreciate that, yeah.

292
00:27:11.671 --> 00:27:12.713
I'll review these.

293
00:27:15.550 --> 00:27:18.052
This is the bullpen here.
That's Booking up there.

294
00:27:18.303 --> 00:27:21.388
The holding cells are down that way.
You wanna see them?

295
00:27:21.681 --> 00:27:23.682
Seen one, seen them all.

296
00:27:24.225 --> 00:27:25.643
This is my desk here, sir.

297
00:27:25.852 --> 00:27:27.227
Nice desk.

298
00:27:27.437 --> 00:27:29.563
Thanks. Let's see....

299
00:27:30.190 --> 00:27:31.315
Brass is on five.

300
00:27:31.524 --> 00:27:32.858
Robbery-Homicide on three.

301
00:27:33.068 --> 00:27:35.069
Over there, that's the tag and bag.

302
00:27:36.446 --> 00:27:39.073
-Through those doors, that's 1 0-1 7.
-Roger.

303
00:27:40.492 --> 00:27:41.825
Show him the rest later.

304
00:27:42.035 --> 00:27:43.577
-Come on.
-Where?

305
00:27:43.870 --> 00:27:46.580
We got a call. Burglary.
It's ours. I'll take this.

306
00:27:46.831 --> 00:27:49.541
-Outside?
-That's where all the crime is.

307
00:27:49.751 --> 00:27:51.919
I just got here,
and that's not a good thing.

308
00:27:52.170 --> 00:27:55.589
I gotta do work in here so that
I know what's going on out there.

309
00:27:55.840 --> 00:27:57.466
I might need backup, right?

310
00:28:00.053 --> 00:28:01.762
How long you been in Burglary?

311
00:28:02.013 --> 00:28:04.598
Me? All my life, man, all my life.

312
00:28:04.849 --> 00:28:09.978
I heard the chief say that you got 1 6
citations. That's incredible. Sixteen.

313
00:28:10.271 --> 00:28:13.524
That's what happens when
your Uncle Lou writes your file.

314
00:28:16.695 --> 00:28:19.113
You can ride up front if you want.

315
00:28:20.865 --> 00:28:22.116
I knew that.

316
00:28:22.534 --> 00:28:26.078
You just gotta be real careful
for the pedestrians coming out here.

317
00:28:26.287 --> 00:28:27.955
Walking around out here.

318
00:28:28.790 --> 00:28:32.292
Am l clear to the right?
Am l clear? Have I got it?

319
00:28:35.296 --> 00:28:36.588
I just made detective.

320
00:28:36.798 --> 00:28:37.923
No kidding.

321
00:28:39.259 --> 00:28:42.803
I worked Traffic for three years.
I got pretty good at it.

322
00:28:45.640 --> 00:28:50.310
You don't have to stop for the yellow.
You could just drive right through.

323
00:28:50.520 --> 00:28:55.482
Sir, not if you'd seen some
of the accidents l've seen. No thanks.

324
00:28:56.276 --> 00:28:58.569
Well, there's your green right there.

325
00:29:02.490 --> 00:29:04.116
Can l ask you a personal question?

326
00:29:04.325 --> 00:29:06.034
Yeah, sure.

327
00:29:06.661 --> 00:29:08.620
How many times did you take the test?

328
00:29:09.914 --> 00:29:13.792
-What test?
-You know, the test for detective.

329
00:29:14.335 --> 00:29:15.461
That one!

330
00:29:15.754 --> 00:29:17.129
-One time.
-Really?

331
00:29:17.589 --> 00:29:19.006
Aced it.

332
00:29:19.841 --> 00:29:21.341
Took it out.

333
00:29:21.551 --> 00:29:23.802
Took me five tries.

334
00:29:24.304 --> 00:29:28.307
I did well on the written part, but my
performance reviews weren't so hot.

335
00:29:28.516 --> 00:29:32.186
How many times did it take you
to get your driver's licence, man?

336
00:29:32.353 --> 00:29:35.147
Please!
Wake me up when we get there.

337
00:29:35.356 --> 00:29:37.107
Yes, sir. I'm sorry.

338
00:29:37.317 --> 00:29:39.193
Goodness, man!

339
00:29:40.320 --> 00:29:42.654
It's a nice suit, sir.
It's really cool.

340
00:29:42.864 --> 00:29:44.531
Well, l appreciate it.

341
00:29:44.699 --> 00:29:46.700
Yeah, you know? Appreciate it.

342
00:29:46.993 --> 00:29:49.620
-Got any music?
-Oh, yeah. Sure.

343
00:29:50.580 --> 00:29:51.872
I like to jam.

344
00:29:52.123 --> 00:29:54.833
Just so long as
we can hear the dispatcher.

345
00:29:56.211 --> 00:29:57.628
That's good.

346
00:29:58.379 --> 00:30:02.382
-l never heard this station before.
-Kind of funky. You like that?

347
00:30:14.062 --> 00:30:17.523
Last night these shelves were loaded
with Elites. Now they're gone.

348
00:30:17.899 --> 00:30:19.399
Three dozen gorgeous rims.

349
00:30:19.651 --> 00:30:21.193
They didn't take anything else?

350
00:30:21.402 --> 00:30:25.531
They went for my good stuff. Chrome
with gold trim. Five grand worth.

351
00:30:26.533 --> 00:30:27.658
What about the alarm?

352
00:30:27.867 --> 00:30:29.743
What about it? It went off.

353
00:30:29.911 --> 00:30:32.079
But it took you guys
two hours to get here.

354
00:30:32.247 --> 00:30:34.498
My wheels are probably
in Tijuana by now.

355
00:30:34.707 --> 00:30:36.250
Here's where they came in.

356
00:30:37.585 --> 00:30:40.587
Looks like they broke the glass,
opened the handle...

357
00:30:40.755 --> 00:30:42.089
...crawled in the window.

358
00:30:42.340 --> 00:30:43.382
Exactly.

359
00:30:43.591 --> 00:30:45.509
Shimmied down the shelf
or something.

360
00:30:45.718 --> 00:30:46.927
This is a waste of time.

361
00:30:47.136 --> 00:30:48.762
That's not how they got in.

362
00:30:49.264 --> 00:30:50.556
Of course it is.

363
00:30:50.890 --> 00:30:52.891
Cut it out.
That's not how they got in.

364
00:30:53.142 --> 00:30:54.268
This is the spot here.

365
00:30:54.435 --> 00:30:56.270
That's how l would've came in.

366
00:30:56.938 --> 00:30:58.772
If l was a thief.

367
00:30:59.023 --> 00:31:00.774
If l was a thief!

368
00:31:00.942 --> 00:31:03.944
Skylight. Just cut the alarm
from the inside.

369
00:31:04.153 --> 00:31:05.946
I could take my time.

370
00:31:06.155 --> 00:31:07.197
Why take your time?

371
00:31:07.699 --> 00:31:09.241
Why would l take my time?

372
00:31:14.038 --> 00:31:15.372
It's heavy.

373
00:31:16.291 --> 00:31:17.791
Now, you tell me.

374
00:31:17.959 --> 00:31:22.754
How long would it take to carry
3 dozen out and load them in a truck?

375
00:31:22.964 --> 00:31:25.757
-Long time.
-lt would take a very long time.

376
00:31:25.967 --> 00:31:29.428
But they probably had three
or four guys working the damn thing--

377
00:31:29.637 --> 00:31:31.972
Zip! Zip the shit up! Frank, hush.

378
00:31:32.307 --> 00:31:34.474
Because you know better. Come on.

379
00:31:34.726 --> 00:31:38.604
Don't lie to me. l'm the man.
I'm the man, Frank.

380
00:31:38.813 --> 00:31:40.230
You're the man.

381
00:31:40.815 --> 00:31:45.319
Your 5000, sorry to tell you,
is worth less than two on the street.

382
00:31:45.570 --> 00:31:48.906
Which don't go four ways
with much juice once you rent a truck.

383
00:31:49.490 --> 00:31:53.201
And to rent a truck,
that requires what?

384
00:31:53.995 --> 00:31:55.495
Credit card...

385
00:31:56.205 --> 00:31:58.332
...driver's licence.

386
00:31:59.250 --> 00:32:00.834
Unless, of course...

387
00:32:01.836 --> 00:32:03.337
...you got your own truck.

388
00:32:05.423 --> 00:32:07.466
He's not gonna let us
search his truck.

389
00:32:07.675 --> 00:32:10.510
What you mean, "let us"?
We the police.

390
00:32:10.720 --> 00:32:12.512
We need a warrant to do that.

391
00:32:12.764 --> 00:32:14.806
We don't even need a key.

392
00:32:16.768 --> 00:32:19.478
Detective, you can't do that.
It's unconstitutional.

393
00:32:20.271 --> 00:32:23.440
Look at that. Look at this.

394
00:32:27.153 --> 00:32:31.114
Look. Solved the crime
my first day on the job!

395
00:32:31.324 --> 00:32:33.825
-We bad detectives.
-There they are!

396
00:32:33.993 --> 00:32:37.871
Filing a false report
is a very serious crime.

397
00:32:41.042 --> 00:32:44.628
I'll handle this. Bring your
weeble-wobble ass over here.

398
00:32:46.881 --> 00:32:49.633
-You like snacks?
-Nothing makes me happier.

399
00:32:49.842 --> 00:32:53.470
You'll be snacking on the bottom
of this shoe if this happens again.

400
00:32:53.680 --> 00:32:55.222
Now, you see them ridges?

401
00:32:55.390 --> 00:32:58.392
These ridges will be imprinted
on the back of your ass...

402
00:32:58.685 --> 00:33:01.144
...permanently if this happens again.

403
00:33:01.354 --> 00:33:02.396
You understand?

404
00:33:02.563 --> 00:33:03.772
Thoroughly understand you.

405
00:33:03.982 --> 00:33:07.818
Every time you look at your ass
there's gonna be a print there.

406
00:33:08.027 --> 00:33:09.820
It's gonna remind you of us.

407
00:33:10.530 --> 00:33:12.155
-And of you lying.
-Right.

408
00:33:12.657 --> 00:33:14.074
Don't wanna see those ridges.

409
00:33:14.367 --> 00:33:18.787
Stop eating cold cuts because
it's seeping through your pores.

410
00:33:18.997 --> 00:33:20.163
Will do.

411
00:33:20.415 --> 00:33:23.000
I'll put one ridge on your ass.

412
00:33:23.501 --> 00:33:26.920
Let's roll. That's cool.
Let's get out of here.

413
00:33:29.215 --> 00:33:31.383
Detective, l know l'm new at this...

414
00:33:31.592 --> 00:33:34.428
...but l thought we were supposed
to arrest the bad guys.

415
00:33:34.721 --> 00:33:36.555
Now he owes us one.

416
00:33:36.764 --> 00:33:38.098
So that's how it works.

417
00:33:38.516 --> 00:33:42.436
We let the little fish go, so that
we can catch the big fish later.

418
00:33:42.687 --> 00:33:44.104
I got it. I got it.

419
00:33:47.358 --> 00:33:50.444
You mind if l drive?
I know a shortcut.

420
00:33:54.741 --> 00:33:56.074
You might wanna buckle up.

421
00:34:04.584 --> 00:34:07.252
Are you in a hurry, sir?

422
00:34:07.462 --> 00:34:10.547
Just testing your car.
Balancing out your shit.

423
00:34:12.884 --> 00:34:15.385
When was the last time
you got all up on this thing?

424
00:34:15.636 --> 00:34:18.055
I've never gotten all up
on anything, sir.

425
00:34:19.265 --> 00:34:22.476
Sometimes you gotta feed
some speed to your ride.

426
00:34:25.146 --> 00:34:26.730
Sir! Watch it!

427
00:34:30.985 --> 00:34:33.904
This is the police!
Move your busted-ass vehicle!

428
00:34:34.405 --> 00:34:36.281
Move, move, move, move, move!

429
00:34:36.491 --> 00:34:38.075
This is the LAPD.

430
00:34:38.284 --> 00:34:39.785
We'll pop one in your ass.

431
00:34:39.994 --> 00:34:41.912
We got guns and shit.

432
00:34:43.289 --> 00:34:44.623
I could get used to this!

433
00:34:45.333 --> 00:34:47.876
I like! l like!

434
00:34:48.086 --> 00:34:49.252
Used to what?

435
00:34:52.173 --> 00:34:55.634
Driving. See, my last partner
did all the driving.

436
00:34:56.177 --> 00:34:57.886
Who was your partner?

437
00:34:59.430 --> 00:35:01.139
I don't wanna talk about it.

438
00:35:01.641 --> 00:35:02.682
Why?

439
00:35:03.101 --> 00:35:07.813
Hey, look, l'm deep, okay? There's
just some places l can't talk about.

440
00:35:08.022 --> 00:35:11.691
We're partners. Gotta communicate.
This thing's like a marriage.

441
00:35:11.943 --> 00:35:14.194
No, this is nothing like a marriage.

442
00:35:14.695 --> 00:35:17.489
-What is it like?
-lt's more like a one-night stand.

443
00:35:17.698 --> 00:35:20.450
Wham, bam, thank you, officer.

444
00:35:25.039 --> 00:35:27.207
-lt's like that?
-lt's like that.

445
00:35:27.708 --> 00:35:31.211
We're just gonna fight crime
and zip the rest of that shit up.

446
00:35:31.462 --> 00:35:32.879
Are you married?

447
00:35:33.131 --> 00:35:34.548
-Girlfriend?
-Not anymore.

448
00:35:34.799 --> 00:35:35.841
What happened?

449
00:35:38.219 --> 00:35:40.011
Work got in the way.

450
00:35:41.055 --> 00:35:42.180
See?

451
00:35:47.353 --> 00:35:49.229
Somebody took out a fire hydrant.

452
00:35:55.820 --> 00:35:58.822
-l'll handle this.
-l gotta get back. I got a headache.

453
00:35:59.031 --> 00:36:00.866
We're on duty.

454
00:36:01.075 --> 00:36:05.078
But l need an aspirin.
A big one, like a hockey puck.

455
00:36:05.246 --> 00:36:06.746
Gentlemen. Excuse me.

456
00:36:06.998 --> 00:36:08.999
Could you come here for a second?

457
00:36:09.584 --> 00:36:11.710
Relax, sir.
Just take it easy for a second.

458
00:36:19.510 --> 00:36:21.094
Morning, officer.

459
00:36:24.390 --> 00:36:26.099
Morning. Where's your aspirins?

460
00:36:26.350 --> 00:36:28.226
Back there by the soda machines.

461
00:36:28.603 --> 00:36:29.603
Appreciate it.

462
00:36:39.864 --> 00:36:42.240
I wanna know how the car
hit the fire hydrant.

463
00:36:44.118 --> 00:36:46.036
-Open the register!
-Don't shoot!

464
00:36:46.287 --> 00:36:47.287
Come on, man!

465
00:36:47.622 --> 00:36:50.040
-Oh, man!
-Come on! The safe too!

466
00:36:58.466 --> 00:36:59.466
Come on.

467
00:37:05.514 --> 00:37:09.309
37-King-5.
Shots fired. Request help.

468
00:37:09.518 --> 00:37:12.062
41 8 West Fifth Street.

469
00:37:19.237 --> 00:37:20.278
Detective Malone!

470
00:37:20.488 --> 00:37:21.571
You okay?

471
00:37:21.822 --> 00:37:22.822
Oh, shit!

472
00:37:25.618 --> 00:37:27.911
Get back! Back! Get back!

473
00:37:28.120 --> 00:37:29.162
Time out, time out.

474
00:37:30.498 --> 00:37:31.665
All right, l'm leaving.

475
00:37:32.166 --> 00:37:33.667
Freeze!

476
00:37:33.918 --> 00:37:36.044
Put your hands on the pavement!

477
00:37:36.254 --> 00:37:38.838
-Hands on the pavement!
-There is no pavement!

478
00:37:39.590 --> 00:37:41.341
Put them on the Oodles of Noodles.

479
00:37:41.592 --> 00:37:43.593
-Put them on the noodles.
-Chicken or beef?

480
00:37:43.803 --> 00:37:44.844
Chicken.

481
00:37:46.305 --> 00:37:49.015
Cool. Cool is good.

482
00:37:49.850 --> 00:37:50.892
Miles?

483
00:37:51.269 --> 00:37:52.310
Tulley?

484
00:37:57.066 --> 00:37:58.108
What are you doing?

485
00:37:58.276 --> 00:38:00.527
What am I doing?
What are you doing?

486
00:38:00.778 --> 00:38:02.696
I'm freaking working over here.

487
00:38:04.490 --> 00:38:05.949
I'm coming in!

488
00:38:06.200 --> 00:38:09.286
Put the gun down!

489
00:38:09.495 --> 00:38:10.996
Detective Malone, talk to me!

490
00:38:11.205 --> 00:38:12.872
Go out the back way!

491
00:38:13.124 --> 00:38:14.874
Go! The back way!

492
00:38:15.209 --> 00:38:16.876
Go out the back way!

493
00:38:17.795 --> 00:38:18.837
Detective, talk to me!

494
00:38:20.673 --> 00:38:21.881
Take two steps back!

495
00:38:23.509 --> 00:38:24.592
What the hell? Go!

496
00:38:26.220 --> 00:38:27.220
Hold it!

497
00:38:29.724 --> 00:38:30.807
Hold your fire!

498
00:38:34.186 --> 00:38:35.729
You okay?

499
00:39:00.379 --> 00:39:01.588
Listen, it's a dead end!

500
00:39:01.839 --> 00:39:03.506
No shit!

501
00:39:08.637 --> 00:39:12.182
He's behind those dumpsters.
He's freaking out. He's got a gun.

502
00:39:15.186 --> 00:39:16.227
Back up!

503
00:39:17.438 --> 00:39:20.440
Get SWAT up here! Sharpshooters
can take him off from the roof.

504
00:39:20.608 --> 00:39:21.900
No!

505
00:39:22.068 --> 00:39:23.610
No sharpshooters.

506
00:39:24.070 --> 00:39:25.111
Why the hell not?

507
00:39:26.864 --> 00:39:28.365
What are you doing here, man?

508
00:39:28.699 --> 00:39:30.700
-Who's he talking to?
-l don't know.

509
00:39:31.160 --> 00:39:34.162
He high, man. He's hallucinating.
Smoking that shit!

510
00:39:34.580 --> 00:39:36.289
He's high.

511
00:39:36.957 --> 00:39:38.708
Put down the gun and come out!

512
00:39:41.754 --> 00:39:43.797
Hold this. Hold on. l'm going in.

513
00:39:44.131 --> 00:39:45.131
What are you doing?

514
00:39:45.758 --> 00:39:47.133
