00:56:48.738 --> 00:56:50.155
Feds are all over it.

764
00:56:50.323 --> 00:56:51.949
That's bullshit!

765
00:56:53.326 --> 00:56:56.495
These boxes contained
an entire Egyptian temple.

766
00:56:56.704 --> 00:56:59.289
Excuse me, here.
Let me see this. Man!

767
00:56:59.499 --> 00:57:00.624
And who are you?

768
00:57:00.834 --> 00:57:03.460
Malone. LAPD.

769
00:57:03.670 --> 00:57:05.421
Agent Gray. FBl.

770
00:57:06.464 --> 00:57:09.174
We'll let you boys in
after we're done.

771
00:57:11.970 --> 00:57:13.470
Look at all this stuff.

772
00:57:13.680 --> 00:57:17.933
Look. They nearly destroyed all this
stuff, and they didn't take none of it.

773
00:57:18.184 --> 00:57:20.310
Look, Officer Malone.

774
00:57:20.520 --> 00:57:21.770
Detective.

775
00:57:21.980 --> 00:57:26.275
You know, you're out of your
jurisdiction, and you're over your head.

776
00:57:26.484 --> 00:57:29.736
I'm over my head?
No, I'm over your head...

777
00:57:29.946 --> 00:57:31.864
...because your head's up your ass.

778
00:57:33.741 --> 00:57:37.870
You're interfering with
a federal investigation, officer.

779
00:57:38.329 --> 00:57:41.123
Now, if you and your bunch
wanna feel important...

780
00:57:41.332 --> 00:57:43.667
...you can help secure
the outer perimeter.

781
00:57:44.461 --> 00:57:45.627
Are we clear?

782
00:57:48.882 --> 00:57:50.632
We clear.

783
00:57:51.134 --> 00:57:52.801
And please...

784
00:57:53.011 --> 00:57:56.763
...tell your men not to touch
anything on their way out.

785
00:57:56.973 --> 00:57:59.808
-lt's like that?
-Yeah, it's like that.

786
00:58:09.986 --> 00:58:11.904
"Head up your ass."
That was great.

787
00:58:12.155 --> 00:58:14.406
I couldn't believe you said that.

788
00:58:14.699 --> 00:58:16.575
He called me "officer."

789
00:58:16.826 --> 00:58:21.747
I'm lead detective.
I have 1 6 citations.

790
00:58:21.915 --> 00:58:23.415
You think that comes easy?

791
00:58:23.583 --> 00:58:26.251
Come on. The guy's nothing
but an FBl asshole.

792
00:58:26.419 --> 00:58:29.421
He thinks we're good for nothing
but sucking down doughnuts.

793
00:58:29.672 --> 00:58:31.590
Let them chase their own
goddamn temple.

794
00:58:31.841 --> 00:58:35.552
They weren't looking for no temple.
They were looking for drugs.

795
00:58:35.762 --> 00:58:37.012
Yes, drugs.

796
00:58:37.222 --> 00:58:39.097
It's the oldest trick in the book.

797
00:58:39.307 --> 00:58:40.390
You smuggle it in...

798
00:58:40.600 --> 00:58:44.937
...boost it before it hits customs,
right? Make it look like a heist.

799
00:58:45.188 --> 00:58:47.064
That's how all the big boys do it.

800
00:58:47.315 --> 00:58:50.234
All they have to do is
look for a truck with a B on it.

801
00:58:50.693 --> 00:58:51.944
What do you mean, B?

802
00:58:52.195 --> 00:58:53.612
"Bonded."

803
00:58:54.030 --> 00:58:57.950
Bonded trucks can get
into bonded warehouses.

804
00:58:58.451 --> 00:58:59.493
Let me ask you:

805
00:59:00.036 --> 00:59:01.745
How do you know all this stuff?

806
00:59:03.623 --> 00:59:06.959
Did a little work
in bonded warehouses.

807
00:59:07.460 --> 00:59:09.711
All right. So what are we waiting for?

808
00:59:10.129 --> 00:59:13.590
Let's do something, all right?
Come on. Call in air support.

809
00:59:14.842 --> 00:59:17.636
Dispatch, this is 37-King-5...

810
00:59:17.887 --> 00:59:21.431
...put me through
to South Bay air support.

811
00:59:27.230 --> 00:59:29.648
1 0-1 2. l've got a white panel truck...

812
00:59:29.857 --> 00:59:34.152
...B-961 , southbound on Wheeler
near Manhattan Beach intersection.

813
00:59:34.404 --> 00:59:36.113
Roger. We're close.

814
00:59:39.826 --> 00:59:40.993
Shit!

815
00:59:45.748 --> 00:59:47.124
Now you're in a hurry?

816
00:59:48.001 --> 00:59:50.836
Sometimes you gotta feed
a little speed to your ride.

817
00:59:51.004 --> 00:59:52.337
You know what l'm saying?

818
01:00:04.183 --> 01:00:05.309
Here we go.

819
01:00:09.314 --> 01:00:10.981
Check out the driver.

820
01:00:12.108 --> 01:00:15.402
Five-feet-six, greasy hair, messy,
very dishevelled and--

821
01:00:15.612 --> 01:00:18.363
Are you a hairdresser
or a detective, man?

822
01:00:19.699 --> 01:00:21.033
That's a jailhouse tat.

823
01:00:21.492 --> 01:00:23.327
Driver did a stretch somewhere.

824
01:00:23.536 --> 01:00:25.287
Ten-twelve. Requesting backup.

825
01:00:25.496 --> 01:00:27.873
LAPD, this is Agent Gray. FBI.

826
01:00:28.041 --> 01:00:31.335
Stand down. I repeat: Stand down.

827
01:00:31.628 --> 01:00:33.128
This is bullshit!

828
01:00:33.338 --> 01:00:36.006
Screw them. Come on! Let's do it!

829
01:00:36.841 --> 01:00:38.383
Come on, you!

830
01:00:40.303 --> 01:00:41.511
Come on, get the door.

831
01:00:41.721 --> 01:00:42.721
Come on!

832
01:00:44.390 --> 01:00:47.059
Drop your weapons!
Put it down.

833
01:00:47.226 --> 01:00:50.437
All right, don't move! Stand still!

834
01:00:50.647 --> 01:00:51.688
Put it down!

835
01:00:52.231 --> 01:00:54.733
Malone! Take him! He's yours!

836
01:00:56.319 --> 01:00:58.737
Don't you run from me! Don't you run!

837
01:00:59.030 --> 01:01:01.198
Let's see those hands, butterball.

838
01:01:03.368 --> 01:01:05.994
Come here!
You wanna make me run?

839
01:01:11.459 --> 01:01:33.605
Come back here!

840
01:01:37.443 --> 01:01:38.610
Bring your ass here!

841
01:01:39.195 --> 01:01:47.536
Come here!

842
01:01:48.246 --> 01:01:50.247
It's okay. Don't worry. l'm a cop.

843
01:01:52.125 --> 01:01:53.375
All right?

844
01:01:54.627 --> 01:01:55.669
Damn!

845
01:02:00.466 --> 01:02:02.718
Don't you know better
than to run from the police?

846
01:02:02.927 --> 01:02:06.555
-l do.
-You got me tired. l don't like tired.

847
01:02:06.723 --> 01:02:09.141
When I get tired, I got ass to whup.

848
01:02:09.767 --> 01:02:12.310
That's what l'm about to do.
Get your ass up!

849
01:02:17.316 --> 01:02:18.567
Bingo.

850
01:02:18.818 --> 01:02:20.485
That's the shit.

851
01:02:25.116 --> 01:02:29.327
We showed them, and
that's what l wanted to do, you know?

852
01:02:29.579 --> 01:02:31.413
-Put this into evidence.
-Exactly.

853
01:02:31.622 --> 01:02:33.331
Evidence. l'll go up with it.

854
01:02:33.583 --> 01:02:35.792
I want you interrogating
those men right now.

855
01:02:36.002 --> 01:02:38.503
No. See, I need to go up
with this stuff...

856
01:02:38.671 --> 01:02:40.922
...and book it into evidence personally.

857
01:02:41.132 --> 01:02:42.174
Why?

858
01:02:43.843 --> 01:02:46.595
I gotta go through it
for clues and shit.

859
01:02:47.138 --> 01:02:50.265
Interrogate the suspects.
Find out where they were going.

860
01:02:50.808 --> 01:02:55.103
When you get them to talk, you can
go through all the evidence you want.

861
01:02:55.313 --> 01:02:57.189
But, sir....

862
01:02:58.107 --> 01:03:02.778
If l get the clue, it'd make for
a better ass-whupping interrogation.

863
01:03:02.987 --> 01:03:04.863
Let's hear it for Detective Malone!

864
01:03:17.376 --> 01:03:20.170
That's it! I want a lawyer.
You cops can't do this.

865
01:03:20.379 --> 01:03:22.005
I got news for you.
I ain't a cop.

866
01:03:24.550 --> 01:03:26.009
God, he's good.

867
01:03:26.219 --> 01:03:28.595
I checked.
West Covina never heard of him.

868
01:03:29.597 --> 01:03:31.681
-So you know.
-Know what?

869
01:03:31.891 --> 01:03:33.308
He's Internal Affairs.

870
01:03:33.518 --> 01:03:35.644
What are you talking about?
He's not I.A.

871
01:03:35.853 --> 01:03:39.105
-He's not?
-Hell, no. He's FBI.

872
01:03:39.649 --> 01:03:41.691
But he hates the FBl.

873
01:03:41.901 --> 01:03:44.903
That's to throw you off.
You think this is an accident?

874
01:03:45.154 --> 01:03:48.740
He knew about the heroin
from the start. FBI planted him here.

875
01:03:48.991 --> 01:03:52.619
Thought he'd get first jump on the
burglary. Afraid we'd screw it up.

876
01:03:52.912 --> 01:03:54.663
Pencil-dicks.

877
01:03:58.251 --> 01:04:00.752
You don't get that training
at the academy.

878
01:04:01.003 --> 01:04:02.754
No, that's old school, man.

879
01:04:02.922 --> 01:04:04.714
You're crushing my head!

880
01:04:07.218 --> 01:04:09.052
That's federal government training.

881
01:04:09.262 --> 01:04:11.847
Like Navy SEAL stuff.

882
01:04:14.392 --> 01:04:16.142
Let's go give him a hand.

883
01:04:18.604 --> 01:04:21.857
All right! All right!
I'll talk! Oh, man!

884
01:04:55.683 --> 01:04:57.559
Look at you.

885
01:04:57.768 --> 01:05:01.229
It was all worth it for you, baby.

886
01:05:07.737 --> 01:05:09.112
What are you doing up there?

887
01:05:10.323 --> 01:05:15.118
I'm just so happy that we're keeping
these drugs off the street.

888
01:05:15.328 --> 01:05:17.996
Get over it. They're going
right back out again.

889
01:05:18.205 --> 01:05:21.124
-Why?
-Because the FBl wants to take it...

890
01:05:21.292 --> 01:05:22.584
...to their lab right away.

891
01:05:22.793 --> 01:05:23.919
Roll it out.

892
01:05:28.507 --> 01:05:29.549
Malone, come on!

893
01:05:29.842 --> 01:05:31.301
Let's go.

894
01:05:32.803 --> 01:05:34.012
Come on, Malone.

895
01:05:47.234 --> 01:05:48.443
Detective.

896
01:05:49.612 --> 01:05:52.322
That heroin belongs to Jean LaFleur.

897
01:05:52.698 --> 01:05:54.324
We've been after him for 5 years.

898
01:05:54.533 --> 01:05:57.494
He keeps shifting his operations
between the U.S. and Mexico.

899
01:05:57.828 --> 01:06:00.163
We're taking it down
to our lab right now.

900
01:06:00.373 --> 01:06:01.873
That's not a good idea.

901
01:06:02.124 --> 01:06:03.166
Why not?

902
01:06:04.669 --> 01:06:06.378
Why don't we just keep it here?

903
01:06:06.629 --> 01:06:10.048
LaFleur doesn't know we have it.
We could use it for bait.

904
01:06:11.384 --> 01:06:12.550
You mean a sting?

905
01:06:12.885 --> 01:06:15.512
Exactly. A sting!

906
01:06:16.389 --> 01:06:20.225
LaFleur expects these drugs
to be in San Diego in three hours.

907
01:06:20.476 --> 01:06:23.812
What kind of sting operation can you
get off the ground before then?

908
01:06:24.480 --> 01:06:27.273
The driver told me one of the guys
on the truck was new.

909
01:06:27.483 --> 01:06:29.567
You can replace him
with somebody else.

910
01:06:29.777 --> 01:06:33.738
Then catch LaFleur when he goes
to pick up the drugs. Bam, got him!

911
01:06:33.906 --> 01:06:35.281
Let me get this straight.

912
01:06:35.491 --> 01:06:39.369
You're volunteering to escort
these drugs into the hands...

913
01:06:39.578 --> 01:06:42.580
...of the most dangerous dealer
in the northern hemisphere?

914
01:06:42.915 --> 01:06:43.915
Hell, no!

915
01:06:44.166 --> 01:06:45.834
What do you need to make it work?

916
01:06:47.378 --> 01:06:49.796
-Me?
-You're the man for the job!

917
01:06:50.006 --> 01:06:52.882
FBI will have tactical command,
but we'll follow your lead.

918
01:06:53.092 --> 01:06:56.052
It's very brave. Let's go.
There's not much time.

919
01:06:56.262 --> 01:06:58.054
Way to go, Malone. Way to go.

920
01:06:58.305 --> 01:07:01.850
-l'm just suggesting some shit.
-We need more men like you!

921
01:07:04.937 --> 01:07:07.939
All right. Hurry up.
Go. Get out of here!

922
01:07:08.232 --> 01:07:10.025
Wait. Hold up. Wait a minute.

923
01:07:10.234 --> 01:07:13.319
You wanted to go.
I'm getting you out of here. Go!

924
01:07:13.571 --> 01:07:16.406
You wouldn't still be here
unless that diamond was here.

925
01:07:16.615 --> 01:07:17.615
I want my cut!

926
01:07:17.867 --> 01:07:21.202
There ain't nothing to cut.
I gotta get the diamond first.

927
01:07:21.454 --> 01:07:22.620
Go get it. l'll wait.

928
01:07:22.872 --> 01:07:25.874
I'm trying to. First, l gotta
run a sting on a drug dealer.

929
01:07:26.250 --> 01:07:27.625
You're a goddamn liar!

930
01:07:27.835 --> 01:07:30.628
Would I make this shit up?
Get out of here!

931
01:07:30.838 --> 01:07:33.965
-l'll see you at Lou's tomorrow.
-l wanna talk about this!

932
01:07:34.133 --> 01:07:36.134
I don't know what you're doing...

933
01:07:36.385 --> 01:07:37.844
...but it ain't gonna work!

934
01:07:38.095 --> 01:07:39.929
And let me get my gun back!

935
01:07:46.395 --> 01:07:50.148
Look. Maybe this isn't
a good idea, you know?

936
01:07:50.399 --> 01:07:53.359
-This is a great idea. lt'll work.
-Brilliant.

937
01:07:53.569 --> 01:07:56.946
-LaFleur's looking for this.
-We know what we're doing, detective.

938
01:07:57.156 --> 01:07:58.907
Oh, l'm a detective now.

939
01:07:59.617 --> 01:08:00.992
Give us a level, please.

940
01:08:02.119 --> 01:08:03.578
All right, detective.

941
01:08:03.788 --> 01:08:07.999
The objective is to have these men
see you as if you were one of them:

942
01:08:08.375 --> 01:08:12.087
A member of the criminal underworld.
It's important your speech...

943
01:08:12.338 --> 01:08:17.175
...and your behaviour are congruent
with their expectation of a criminal.

944
01:08:17.384 --> 01:08:20.011
I get it. Sort of "walk the walk."

945
01:08:20.262 --> 01:08:21.304
That's right.

946
01:08:21.680 --> 01:08:24.265
You have to look, act...

947
01:08:24.475 --> 01:08:26.768
...and even think like a criminal.

948
01:08:26.977 --> 01:08:28.770
Change your speech patterns too.

949
01:08:29.021 --> 01:08:33.191
Criminals like to use slang
terminology, profanity and so forth...

950
01:08:33.400 --> 01:08:36.694
...especially with regard to police
and authority figures.

951
01:08:36.987 --> 01:08:39.697
You mean like, "Shut the hell up,
you dickless FBl--"

952
01:08:39.949 --> 01:08:41.699
-That's right.
-"You stupid ass."

953
01:08:41.951 --> 01:08:43.326
-That'll do.
-"You tight--"

954
01:08:43.536 --> 01:08:44.702
Enough!

955
01:08:46.539 --> 01:08:47.622
All right, listen up.

956
01:08:47.832 --> 01:08:49.541
LaFleur's a killer.

957
01:08:49.792 --> 01:08:54.546
If he senses anything amiss, Malone
is gonna be in one hell of a tight spot.

958
01:08:59.927 --> 01:09:03.346
If anything happens to me,
forget everything l ever told you.

959
01:09:03.556 --> 01:09:05.640
You mean about lnternal Affairs?

960
01:09:05.850 --> 01:09:07.642
No, Carlson. I mean about everything.

961
01:09:07.977 --> 01:09:09.936
Detective, saddle up.

962
01:09:10.146 --> 01:09:11.729
Good luck.

963
01:09:16.193 --> 01:09:19.070
Carlson, remember. Forget it!

964
01:09:19.238 --> 01:09:20.405
Time to go.

965
01:09:22.992 --> 01:09:24.033
Detective.

966
01:09:24.535 --> 01:09:28.329
If my client gets a scratch
on him while he's in your custody...

967
01:09:28.539 --> 01:09:33.543
...l'll see your badge is revoked
and you're thrown in jail. Okay?

968
01:09:33.752 --> 01:09:35.253
You can't touch me.

969
01:09:38.424 --> 01:09:42.093
He'll be fine, counsellor. Malone,
let's get this show on the road.

970
01:09:43.179 --> 01:09:44.846
Drive. Buckle up.

971
01:09:47.892 --> 01:09:50.393
-Give me video.
-Let's get one thing straight.

972
01:09:50.603 --> 01:09:53.271
This is my side here
and that's your side there.

973
01:09:53.522 --> 01:09:55.732
Stay on your side
and l'm gonna stay on mine.

974
01:09:56.442 --> 01:09:59.110
Gentlemen.
Keep the chatter to a minimum.

975
01:09:59.361 --> 01:10:02.405
You don't like the show,
change the channel.

976
01:10:02.781 --> 01:10:04.949
And keep this channel clear.

977
01:10:08.704 --> 01:10:10.538
Who is this guy?

978
01:10:10.998 --> 01:10:12.081
That's Malone.

979
01:10:13.792 --> 01:10:15.251
I can't drive if you do that.

980
01:10:15.794 --> 01:10:17.212
Drive!

981
01:10:36.899 --> 01:10:38.316
We're coming up on our exit.

982
01:10:40.236 --> 01:10:43.488
All units, this is Gray.
Fall back and keep your distance.

983
01:10:53.791 --> 01:10:55.250
We're approaching the site.

984
01:10:55.459 --> 01:10:57.794
LAPD, take the south side.
We'll take the north.

985
01:11:22.778 --> 01:11:25.321
They're headed into warehouse 3.

986
01:11:25.572 --> 01:11:27.699
Focus in. Closer.

987
01:11:35.708 --> 01:11:36.749
This is it.

988
01:11:36.917 --> 01:11:38.793
-You sure?
-Yeah. Warehouse 3.

989
01:11:39.128 --> 01:11:43.381
All right, Benny, sit tight
and keep your mouth shut.

990
01:11:43.632 --> 01:11:44.841
Thanks for the tip.

991
01:11:51.473 --> 01:11:52.682
What's Malone doing?

992
01:12:00.482 --> 01:12:02.400
They're coming in behind you.

993
01:12:02.609 --> 01:12:04.527
Get ready. Here he comes.

994
01:12:09.575 --> 01:12:11.826
That's what l'm talking about!

995
01:12:12.619 --> 01:12:14.704
-That's the shit.
-You're right!

996
01:12:14.913 --> 01:12:17.123
All 500 kilos!

997
01:12:17.916 --> 01:12:21.127
What are you talking about?
Let's get out! l want my cut!

998
01:12:21.337 --> 01:12:23.421
-You still got it?
-We still have a signal.

999
01:12:23.672 --> 01:12:24.756
It's just distorted.

1000
01:12:25.924 --> 01:12:27.133
Can you hear him?

1001
01:12:27.343 --> 01:12:30.511
We can't get out of here, okay?
They got cops everywhere.

1002
01:12:30.721 --> 01:12:34.057
-So? You're one of them.
-No, no, no.

1003
01:12:34.224 --> 01:12:35.433
I'm a drug dealer now.

1004
01:12:35.934 --> 01:12:38.895
Man, listen to me.
You're a jewel thief.

1005
01:12:39.438 --> 01:12:41.606
I'm a drug dealer now!

1006
01:12:41.774 --> 01:12:44.442
Why you selling this
when you got that diamond?

1007
01:12:45.194 --> 01:12:46.361
Just like old times.

1008
01:12:47.237 --> 01:12:49.072
I don't believe that shit!

1009
01:12:51.116 --> 01:12:52.283
Is this a reunion?

